pageTitle: Osman Tolga ARICAK | Office of International Programs
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {1826=O. Tolga Aricak received his B.A. degree in Counseling and Guidance Program from Istanbul University in 1993, M.A. degree in Psychological Services in Education in 1995, and PhD in Educational Sciences from the Marmara University Istanbul in 1999. He worked at Trakya University School of Education as assistant professor between 1999-2006 years. In the 2006-2007 academic year, Dr. Aricak worked at Department of Counseling & Educational Psychology, Indiana University Bloomington as research scholar. He conducted several research projects with colleagues in Indiana University Bloomington. He also worked as assistant professor at Department of Psychology in Tulane University New Orleans in 2007-2008 academic year. He is currently associate professor at Department of Psychology in Fatih University Istanbul. His current research is focused on Cyberbullying among adolescents. }
